    <string name="tutorial_page_enable_description">To get started, you need to enable Pastiera as an input method in Android Settings. Tap the button below to open settings.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_select_title">Select Pastiera</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_select_description">To use Pastiera, select it among the input methods. Pick between the full IME UI with the &quot;Use on-screen keyboard&quot; toggle ON or the minimal &quot;Pastierina&quot; UI with the toggle OFF.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_led_title">LED Indicator</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_led_description">To get the most out of Pastiera, set the Fn key to act as Ctrl from Android system settings. The IME bar shows four LEDs: they turn blue when the modifier is active one-shot and orange when it is locked. The SYM layout LED is blue on the emoji page and orange on the symbols page.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_nav_mode_title">Nav Mode</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_nav_mode_description">Nav Mode lets you navigate the device UI with letter shortcuts such as IJKL or ESDF.\nTo activate:\n• Press Ctrl twice quickly\n• Letter keys become navigation controls\n• Press Ctrl again to exit\nEvery shortcut can be remapped in Advanced Settings.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_customization_title">Customization</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_customization_description">Pastiera offers many customization options:\n• Customizable keyboard layouts\n• Launcher shortcuts &amp; Power Shortcuts\n• IME bar can act as a swipe bar to move the cursor\n• Custom mappings for Nav Mode\nExplore the settings to find the perfect configuration for you!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_ready_title">Ready to Start</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page_ready_description">You are now ready to use Pastiera! Remember that you can always return to settings to further customize the keyboard to your needs.</string>
